The story actually dates back to September, when this teacher asked her students, aged 6/7 years old, to choose a name for the class's fur bear.
“Eight names come out of the children’s mouths, including Hassan, Abdullah and Mohammed,” said school director Robert Boulos.
Finally, after a vote in the classroom, 20 out of 23 children chose Mohammed as their favourite name.
Mohammed is of course the name of the Muslim prophet, but above all a very common name in Sudan.
