Like the alleged homosexuality or mental disability of some victims of deportation.
The records of concentration camps or Gestapo arrest warrants had been collected after the war for a practical purpose: to find the civilians deported or subjected to compulsory labor and, eventually, to provide them with proof of their internment, in order to pave the way for their compensation.
Even today, in Bad Arolsen, more than 300 permanent employees handle tens of thousands of individual requests.
