Which insurance is suitable for me?
Car insurance, which covers the driver against possible accidents, involves a significant expense that will depend on various factors, such as age, gender, the age of the driver’s license, civil status, the type of vehicle to be insured or the use that is made of it, among others.
Having a car is the main thing.
Choosing the right car is even more difficult than choosing the right car.
And that is, choosing the right car insurance is even more difficult than choosing the model of the vehicle.
Car insurance is an agreement between an insurance company and the insurer.
This compromise is materialized by an insurance contract, which establishes that the company receives the value of the awarded premium and in exchange it becomes responsible for the obligation to pay compensation in case of disaster.
The premium is the price of the insurance, which is established by taking into account various factors, such as age, gender, the age of the driving license, civil status, the type of vehicle to be insured or the use that is made of it, among others.
Insurance companies set their prices based on statistics, so that the higher the probability of an accident, the higher the odds to be paid.
This is why people over the age of 25 and women have to pay lower premiums, as statistics show that these people have a lower rate of accidents due to their caution.
Similarly, using censuses, companies concluded that married people tend to have fewer accidents than single drivers.
The use of the vehicle will affect the frequency, and therefore the likelihood of an accident.
As the frequency increases, the probability increases.
There are many variables that insurance companies take into account when determining the premium price.
This is why the driver must carefully study the situation to choose the car insurance that best suits his profile.
We will here expose the most significant variables when choosing one or the other type of insurance, so that it, in addition to adapting to the characteristics of the insurer, offers a reasonable price.
Young people under the age of 25 face various disadvantages when signing an affordable insurance contract, such as low driving experience and the age of the driving license.
While the ideal thing to be well insured is a full-risk insurance, there are other more economical options.
The most foreseeable drivers can opt for an all-risk insurance with freedom, so that they get the coverage of an all-risk insurance but at a more affordable price.
This form of agreement implies that the customer pays a part of the damage amount.
"The portion of the amount of damages that the customer pays will be established based on the value of the premium, which will be higher the lower the amount will be," specifies Luis Noguera, the head in Spain of First Europa, an online insurance mediator.
Another option is extended third-party insurance, so that the customer provides protection to deal with damages caused to third parties, but by for those caused on his own car.
In addition, it would be covered against theft, fires and loss of the vehicle.
and a counsel.
If you are under the age of 25, try to be careful and avoid damages as much as possible, as this will affect the bonus, which may reduce the price of the insurance in the future.
A bonus is a reduction in the base rate that the company has.
On the contrary, a penalty is an increase in the base rate.
“Bonuses and penalties will depend on the company and its profits.
If the company has had a good year it will be able to afford to increase the bonuses, "clarifies Noguera.
After the age of 25, it becomes easier for drivers when signing an insurance contract, as the rate of accidents is reduced thanks to accumulated experience.
That is why it is best to choose an insurance with all risk frankly.
“Normally, young people cannot take advantage of the experience acquired in advance after an accident,” the director of the European car company in Spain assures, adding that the majority of accidents occur during the second year of driving, once the ‘fear of the novice’ has passed.
However, if the customer is married but does not yet have children it is best that he negotiates insurance at all risks, as long as his economic situation allows him to do so.
Marriages with children are considered by insurers to be the people with the lowest rate of damages, because the surcharges will be lower.
In this case, the best insurance would be an all-risk insurance with franchise (which can be 300 euros), or an extended third-party insurance from the third year of the vehicle’s life when the insured has a high level of bonus.
"They have a more casual drive and they have greater purchasing power to afford the luxury of taking on a larger amount of franchises," Luis Noguera judges.
For retirees an all-risk insurance with franchise is preferable (this being the one of 150 euros), or an extended third-party insurance when the insurer has a high level of bonus.
It must be said that car insurance is something important, not only because it covers the driver in the face of possible accidents, but also because it represents a significant expense, which is why it is fundamental to properly study the insurance that best suits us according to our personal situation.
